Subject: P vs NP Toy CSP Coherence Model 001

Description: A deliberately limited formal toy model translating the source document's resonance/coherence language into a CSP-shaped object without promoting it to P vs NP proof authority.

& [ToyModel] is a proof-inquiry artifact
  + [event_uuid] is 559b15d2-8246-46fb-8229-15ff9432ae31
  + [project] is seven math problems
  + [problem] is P versus NP
  + [source_analysis] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\seven_math_problems\document_analysis\P_vs_NP_Document_Analysis.sop
  + [translation_gate] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\seven_math_problems\proof_inquiry\P_vs_NP_CSP_Coherence_Translation_Gate.sop
  + [prior_gate_application] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\events\proof_inquiry\2026-06-26_p_vs_np_csp_coherence_translation_gate_001.sop
  + [authority_status] is exploratory_model_not_solution

& [FormalToyCSP] is the model
  + [variables] is X_1 through X_n, representing local symbolic positions or decision sites
  + [domain] is a finite phase alphabet D
  + [constraints] is a set of local relations R_i over bounded-size variable scopes
  + [coherence_condition] is an assignment a: {X_1,...,X_n} -> D satisfying every relation R_i
  + [certificate] is the full assignment a
  + [verifier] is check each listed relation against a in time polynomial in the encoded instance size
  + [source_mapping] is phase coherence becomes simultaneous satisfaction of local compatibility relations

& [CoherenceOperator] is the candidate formal operation
  + [operator_name] is local propagation with repair
  + [input] is partial assignment and constraint list
  + [step] is remove locally inconsistent domain values, propagate forced choices, and revise conflicting local assignments
  + [possible_success_case] is acyclic, bounded-treewidth, Horn-like, bijunctive, affine, or otherwise tractable restricted structure
  + [known_failure_shape] is local consistency can hold while global satisfiability fails in hard CSP families
  + [runtime_shape] is polynomial for bounded local propagation passes, but not guaranteed complete for arbitrary NP-complete instances

& [GateEvaluation] is the CSP coherence translation result
  + [lock_001_variables_domains_constraints] is passed_for_toy_model
  + [lock_002_certificate_verifier] is passed_for_toy_model
  + [lock_003_constraint_language_scope] is restricted_or_unspecified
  + [lock_004_coherence_operator] is partial
  + [lock_005_algorithmic_effect] is partial_for_tractable_fragments_failed_for_general_np_complete_scope
  + [lock_006_complexity_status] is polynomial_as_propagation_incomplete_as_solver
  + [lock_007_claim_route] is tractable_subclass_laboratory

& [MeaningYield] is what this model finds
  + [meaning_001] is the source proposition becomes mathematically sharper when recast as a question about which constraint structures allow local coherence to determine global solution
  + [meaning_002] is resonance key becomes a formal invariant or closure operation only after a constraint language is chosen
  + [meaning_003] is the toy model supports algorithmic intuition but not P equals NP
  + [meaning_004] is the hard frontier is precisely whether any source-derived coherence operator is complete on an NP-complete family

& [Disposition] is the lane status
  + [solution_status] is no_solution_found
  + [best_current_shape] is CSP translation yields a tractable-subclass research program and a clean overclaim detector
  + [open_lock] is no source-derived polynomial-time complete solver for SAT, 3-SAT, or an NP-complete CSP family
  + [recommended_next] is either pivot to SAT/3-SAT lower-resolution research or pause P vs NP and run project Git reflection before Yang-Mills
  + [heartbeat_status] is active every minute
